{
    "id": "vectorutil",
    "lang": "en-us",
    "name": "VectorUtil",
    "description": "Build and work with vector3 values — the (x, y, z) used for positions and directions. Make them, measure distance, find directions, and blend between them.",
    "link": "/docs/uniscript/en-us/vectorutil",
    "tags": [
        "uniscript",
        "vectorutil",
        "vector3",
        "position",
        "direction",
        "distance"
    ],
    "previous": {
        "name": "UniObjectUtil",
        "link": "/docs/uniscript/en-us/uniobjectutil"
    },
    "next": {
        "name": "QuaternionUtil",
        "link": "/docs/uniscript/en-us/quaternionutil"
    },
    "content": [
        {
            "id": "block-001",
            "tag": "h1",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "VectorUtil"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-002",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "A **vector3** is three numbers bundled together — `(x, y, z)`. It's how the game describes a **position** (where something is) and a **direction** (which way it points or moves). `VectorUtil` is the toolbox for building and working with these values."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-003",
            "tag": "note",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "In Universe, `x` is left/right, `y` is up/down, and `z` is forward/back."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-004",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Making a vector"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-005",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Use `New` to build your own, or grab one of the ready-made common directions:"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-006",
            "tag": "code",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "lines": [
                "// Build a point 5 units up.",
                "vector3 spot = VectorUtil.New(0.0, 5.0, 0.0);",
                "",
                "// Ready-made directions.",
                "vector3 up      = VectorUtil.Up();       // (0, 1, 0)",
                "vector3 forward = VectorUtil.Forward();  // (0, 0, 1)",
                "vector3 origin  = VectorUtil.Zero();     // (0, 0, 0)"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-007",
            "tag": "table",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "headers": [
                "Method",
                "Gives you"
            ],
            "rows": [
                ["`New(x, y, z)`", "A custom vector from three numbers."],
                ["`Zero()`", "`(0, 0, 0)` — the origin / no movement."],
                ["`One()`", "`(1, 1, 1)` — handy as a default scale."],
                ["`Up()` / `Down()`", "`(0, 1, 0)` / `(0, -1, 0)`."],
                ["`Left()` / `Right()`", "`(-1, 0, 0)` / `(1, 0, 0)`."],
                ["`Forward()` / `Back()`", "`(0, 0, 1)` / `(0, 0, -1)`."]
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-008",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Reading the parts"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-009",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "`X`, `Y`, and `Z` pull a single number back out of a vector — for example, to check how high something is."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-010",
            "tag": "code",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "lines": [
                "vector3 pos = UniObjectUtil.GetPosition(this);",
                "float height = VectorUtil.Y(pos);",
                "if (height < -10.0)",
                "{",
                "    Debug.Log(\"Fell off the map!\");",
                "}"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-011",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Distance and length"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-012",
            "tag": "table",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "headers": [
                "Method",
                "What it does"
            ],
            "rows": [
                ["`Distance(a, b)`", "How far apart two points are — perfect for \"is the player close enough?\"."],
                ["`Magnitude(v)`", "The length of a vector (e.g. how fast something is moving)."],
                ["`Normalized(v)`", "Shrinks a vector to length 1, keeping its direction — a pure direction with no speed."]
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-013",
            "tag": "code",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "lines": [
                "// Open a door only when the player is within 3 units.",
                "float dist = VectorUtil.Distance(playerPos, doorPos);",
                "if (dist < 3.0)",
                "{",
                "    OpenDoor();",
                "}"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-014",
            "tag": "tip",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Use `Normalized` whenever you want a **direction** without caring about length — like pushing something \"toward the target\" at your own chosen speed: `direction = VectorUtil.Normalized(targetPos - myPos)`."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-015",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Blending between vectors"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-016",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Just like numbers, you can smoothly move from one point to another. This is how you glide objects instead of teleporting them."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-017",
            "tag": "table",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "headers": [
                "Method",
                "What it does"
            ],
            "rows": [
                ["`Lerp(from, to, t)`", "A point partway from `from` to `to`, where `t` is `0`–`1`."],
                ["`SmoothLerp(from, to, speed)`", "An ease toward `to` at `speed`. It already accounts for frame time, so just pass a speed (e.g. `5.0`) — no need to multiply by delta time."]
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-018",
            "tag": "code",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "lines": [
                "// Glide an object toward a target spot each frame.",
                "vector3 here = UniObjectUtil.GetPosition(this);",
                "vector3 next = VectorUtil.SmoothLerp(here, targetPos, 5.0);",
                "UniObjectUtil.SetPosition(this, next);"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-019",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Advanced direction math"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-020",
            "tag": "table",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "headers": [
                "Method",
                "What it does"
            ],
            "rows": [
                ["`Dot(a, b)`", "Tells how much two directions point the same way: `1` = same, `0` = at a right angle, `-1` = opposite. Great for \"is the target in front of me?\"."],
                ["`Cross(a, b)`", "Gives a direction at a right angle to both inputs."],
                ["`Project(v, normal)`", "Flattens vector `v` onto a surface defined by `normal` — for example, keeping movement along the ground."]
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-021",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Full method reference"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-022",
            "tag": "table",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "headers": [
                "Returns",
                "Method",
                "Parameters"
            ],
            "rows": [
                ["`vector3`", "`Zero`", "—"],
                ["`vector3`", "`Up`", "—"],
                ["`vector3`", "`Down`", "—"],
                ["`vector3`", "`Left`", "—"],
                ["`vector3`", "`Right`", "—"],
                ["`vector3`", "`Forward`", "—"],
                ["`vector3`", "`Back`", "—"],
                ["`vector3`", "`One`", "—"],
                ["`vector3`", "`New`", "`float x, float y, float z`"],
                ["`vector3`", "`Lerp`", "`vector3 from, vector3 to, float speed`"],
                ["`vector3`", "`SmoothLerp`", "`vector3 from, vector3 to, float speed`"],
                ["`float`", "`Magnitude`", "`vector3 vector`"],
                ["`vector3`", "`Normalized`", "`vector3 vector`"],
                ["`vector3`", "`Cross`", "`vector3 vector1, vector3 vector2`"],
                ["`float`", "`Dot`", "`vector3 vector1, vector3 vector2`"],
                ["`vector3`", "`Project`", "`vector3 vector, vector3 normal`"],
                ["`float`", "`X`", "`vector3 vector`"],
                ["`float`", "`Y`", "`vector3 vector`"],
                ["`float`", "`Z`", "`vector3 vector`"],
                ["`float`", "`Distance`", "`vector3 a, vector3 b`"]
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-023",
            "tag": "tip",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Vectors describe positions and directions; **rotations** are a different value called a quaternion. To turn a direction into a facing, see [QuaternionUtil](/docs/uniscript/en-us/quaternionutil)."
        }
    ]
}
